{"type":"message","id":"b3e751d0","parentId":"450c30fc","timestamp":"2026-03-25T21:40:36.694Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to proceed with Step 3 of Phase 2: Reviewer. I should create the review configuration and integration.\n\nLet me create:\n1. `registry/review-config.yaml` - Review settings\n2. Integration with the existing hook system\n\nI'll follow the minimal principle and create a simple, functional review system that integrates with what we have.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Verstanden. Ich erstelle den Reviewer."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_P0tYR3oXCfMygNfLJOTgjYDH","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Review Configuration - Phase 2 Minimal\n# Format: YAML 1.2\n\nversion: \"1.0\"\nlast_updated: \"2026-03-25T22:40:00+01:00\"\n\n# Review-Engine Einstellungen\nengine:\n  enabled: true\n  default_trigger: \"on_error\"  # always | on_error | manual\n  auto_review: false           # Automatisches Review bei jedem Plan\n  require_approval: false      # Manuelle Freigabe erforderlich?\n  \n# Review-Typen\ntypes:\n  plan_review:\n    description: \"Review nach Plan-Ausführung\"\n    enabled: true\n    trigger: \"on_error\"\n    checklist:\n      - \"Alle Schritte ausgeführt?\"\n      - \"Erfolgskriterien erfüllt?\"\n      - \"Keine Seiteneffekte?\"\n      - \"Dokumentation aktualisiert?\"\n      - \"Rollback-Info notiert?\"\n    \n  execution_review:\n    description: \"Review nach Tool-Ausführung\"\n    enabled: true\n    trigger: \"on_error\"\n    scope:\n      - \"file_operations\"\n      - \"exec\"\n      - \"web_search\"\n    \n  error_review:\n    description: \"Review bei Fehlern\"\n    enabled: true\n    trigger: \"always\"\n    auto_create_ticket: true\n\n# Integrationen\nintegrations:\n  self_improving:\n    enabled: true\n    skill_id: \"self-improving-andrew\"\n    feedback_file: \"memory/self-improving/review-feedback.md\"\n    patterns_file: \"memory/self-improving/review-patterns.md\"\n    \n  hooks:\n    enabled: true\n    hook_id: \"review:post_execution\"\n    handler_file: \"hooks/review-post-execution.md\"\n    \n  plans:\n    enabled: true\n    plan_template_reference: \"plans/TEMPLATE.md#review\"\n\n# Review-Output\noutput:\n  format: \"markdown\"\n  location: \"memory/reviews/\"\n  naming: \"{timestamp}_{plan_id}_review.md\"\n  include_diff: true\n  include_suggestions: true\n\n# Qualitäts-Thresholds\nthresholds:\n  min_success_rate: 0.8      # 80% Schritte müssen erfolgreich\n  max_severity_allowed: \"medium\"  # Keine \"high\" Severity erlaubt\n  require_rollback_plan: true\n\n# Eskalation\nescalation:\n  enabled: true\n  on_high_severity: \"notify_user\"\n  on_repeated_failures: \"require_manual_review\"\n  max_auto_retries: 2\n","file_path":"C:/Users/andre/.openclaw/workspace/registry/review-config.yaml"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":3646,"output":745,"cacheRead":75008,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79399,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774474820897}}
{"type":"message","id":"f4bea5f8","parentId":"b3e751d0","timestamp":"2026-03-25T21:40:36.712Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_P0tYR3oXCfMygNfLJOTgjYDH","toolName":"write","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully wrote 1947 bytes to C:/Users/andre/.openclaw/workspace/registry/review-config.yaml"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774474836707}}
{"type":"message","id":"93c24e3d","parentId":"f4bea5f8","timestamp":"2026-03-25T21:41:00.945Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, now I need to create the review hook handler file that integrates with the hook engine.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_2uX4UkgCJGepKJ0iBpMz5FAG","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Hook: Post-Execution Review\n# Trigger: Nach Ausführung von Plans oder kritischen Operationen\n# Hook-ID: review:post_execution\n# Priorität: 150 (nach session:end, vor cleanup)\n\n## Beschreibung\nDieser Hook führt automatisierte Reviews durch nach:\n- Plan-Ausführung\n- Kritischen Tool-Operationen (file, exec)\n- Fehlern/Exceptions\n\n## Trigger-Bedingungen\n\n```yaml\nhook:\n  id: \"review:post_execution\"\n  triggers:\n    - event: \"plan:completed\"\n      condition: \"review_required == true\"\n      \n    - event: \"plan:failed\"\n      condition: \"always\"\n      severity: \"high\"\n      \n    - event: \"tool:executed\"\n      tool: [\"write\", \"edit\", \"exec\"]\n      condition: \"review_config.execution_review.enabled\"\n      \n    - event: \"error:critical\"\n      condition: \"always\"\n      immediate: true\n```\n\n## Review-Prozess\n\n### 1. Prüfung auslösen\n```\nIF plan.status == \"failed\" THEN\n  review_triggered = true\n  review_type = \"error_review\"\nELSE IF plan.review_required == true THEN\n  review_triggered = true\n  review_type = \"plan_review\"\nELSE IF tool.category in [\"destructive\", \"critical\"] THEN\n  review_triggered = true\n  review_type = \"execution_review\"\n```\n\n### 2. Review durchführen\n```\n1. Lade review-config.yaml\n2. Identifiziere Review-Typ\n3. Führe Checkliste durch\n4. Bewerte Severity (low/medium/high)\n5. Generiere Vorschläge\n6. Speichere Review-Ergebnis\n```\n\n### 3. Integration mit self-improving-andrew\n```\nIF review.findings.include?(\"pattern\") THEN\n  write_to: \"memory/self-improving/review-patterns.md\"\n  format: \"Pattern: {description}\\nCorrection: {solution}\\n\"\nEND\n\nIF review.feedback.present? THEN\n  write_to: \"memory/self-improving/review-feedback.md\"\n  format: \"[{timestamp}] {context}: {feedback}\\n\"\nEND\n```\n\n## Review-Output-Format\n\n```markdown\n# Review: {plan_id}\n**Datum:** {timestamp}\n**Typ:** {review_type}\n**Auslöser:** {trigger}\n\n## Zusammenfassung\n- Status: {passed | failed | partial}\n- Erfolgsrate: {X}/{Y} Schritte ({Z}%)\n- Severity: {low | medium | high}\n\n## Checkliste\n- [x] Alle Schritte ausgeführt?\n- [ ] Erfolgskriterien erfüllt?\n- [x] Keine Seiteneffekte?\n...\n\n## Gefundene Probleme\n| # | Problem | Schwere | Lösung |\n|---|---------|---------|--------|\n| 1 | {Beschreibung} | medium | {Fix} |\n\n## Vorschläge\n1. {Verbesserungsvorschlag}\n2. {Verbesserungsvorschlag}\n\n## Feedback für self-improving-andrew\n```\n{Extrahierte Patterns}\n```\n\n## Aktionen\n- [ ] Manuelles Review erforderlich\n- [ ] Rollback empfohlen\n- [x] Auto-korrektur möglich\n```\n\n## Integration mit Plans\n\n### In Plan-Template verfügbar\n```yaml\nreview:\n  status: \"completed\"\n  result: \"passed\"\n  severity: \"low\"\n  findings: 0\n  reviewed_by: \"auto\"\n  reviewed_at: \"2026-03-25T22:40:00+01:00\"\n```\n\n### Manuelle Review-Anforderung\n```bash\n# Trigger manuelles Review\nopenclaw review:trigger plan-id\n\n# Review-Status prüfen\nopenclaw review:status plan-id\n```\n\n## Konfiguration\n\nReview-Regeln werden definiert in:\n- `registry/review-config.yaml`\n\n## Fehlerbehandlung\n\n### Wenn Review selbst fehlschlägt\n```\nLog: \"Review failed: {error}\"\nNotify: user (if critical)\nContinue: true (nicht blockierend)\n```\n\n### Wenn self-improving Skill nicht verfügbar\n```\nLog: \"Skill 'self-improving-andrew' not available\"\nSave to: \"memory/reviews/orphaned-feedback-{timestamp}.md\"\nRetry: false\n```\n\n## Status\n\n- [x] Hook-Definition erstellt\n- [x] Review-Config erstellt\n- [ ] Automatische Trigger-Integration (Phase 2+)\n- [ ] Implementierung Review-Logik (Phase 2+)\n\n---\n\n**Hinweis:** Dies ist ein Template. Die tatsächliche Ausführung erfolgt über\ndie Hook-Engine wenn die Trigger-Integration implementiert wird.\n","file_path":"C:/Users/andre/.openclaw/workspace/hooks/review-post-execution.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":845,"output":1257,"cacheRead":78592,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":80694,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774474836716}}
