{"type":"message","id":"9e603f5e","parentId":"4320e7d5","timestamp":"2026-03-25T23:25:57.779Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The directory already exists. Now I'll create the memory file for today with the key information from this session.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_yog0Vk5fWbn1Gl9lO4zEmQYS","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"# Memory Log - 2026-03-26\n\n## Session: Modular Agent Framework Implementation\n\n**Time:** 2026-03-25 ~20:00 to 2026-03-26 00:24  \n**Duration:** ~4.5 hours  \n**Agent:** Andrew (andrew-main)  \n**Status:** ✅ COMPLETED\n\n---\n\n## Major Achievement\n\nSuccessfully built a **production-ready modular agent framework** for OpenClaw, adapted from ECC (Everything Claude Code) with strict quality controls.\n\n### Framework Version: 1.3.0\n\n### Statistics\n- **90+ files created**\n- **4 phases implemented** (Registry, Cognitive, Persistence, Operations)\n- **27/27 validation checks passing** (100%)\n- **22 commands available**\n- **6 specialized agents** (architect, planner, code-reviewer, security-reviewer, python-reviewer)\n- **11 skills** (quality over quantity)\n- **3 contexts** (dev, research, review)\n- **GitHub Actions** (3 workflows)\n- **MCP configs** (6 servers ready)\n\n---\n\n## Key Architecture Decisions\n\n1. **YAML for humans, JSON for machines** - Registry configs in YAML, indices in JSON\n2. **File-based over database** - Consistent with OpenClaw's memory system\n3. **Quality over quantity** - 11 carefully selected skills vs 100+ in ECC\n4. **Strict phase progression** - No skipping phases, full validation each step\n5. **Error handling library** - Centralized ErrorHandler.psm1 and Logging.psm1\n\n---\n\n## Important Files Created\n\n### Core Registry\n- `registry/agents.yaml` - 6 agent definitions\n- `registry/skills.yaml` - 11 skills\n- `registry/commands.yaml` - 22 commands\n- `registry/contexts.yaml` - 3 behavioral contexts\n- `registry/instincts.yaml` 