{"type":"message","id":"6ac70e80","parentId":"82f667f7","timestamp":"2026-03-25T23:26:32.089Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if there's a stronger AI model than kimi-coding/k2p5 | think low that they can select.\n\nFrom my context, I can see:\n- Current model: kimi-coding/k2p5\n- Default model: kimi-coding/kimi-k2-thinking\n- The user mentioned \"think low\" - this refers to the thinking level\n\nLooking at the available models mentioned in my system:\n- kimi-coding/k2p5 - This is what I'm currently using\n- kimi-coding/kimi-k2-thinking - This is the default model mentioned\n- The user can also use model aliases like \"Kimi for Coding: kimi-coding/k2p5\"\n\nI should check what models are available. From the context, I see:\n- kimi-coding/k2p5 (current)\n- kimi-coding/kimi-k2-thinking (default)\n\nBut the user is asking for something STRONGER. The k2p5 is already a strong model. The kimi-k2-thinking might be different - it could be the thinking model.\n\nActually, looking more carefully:\n- \"kimi-coding/k2p5\" is the current model\n- \"kimi-coding/kimi-k2-thinking\" is the default model\n\nThe user mentioned \"think low\" which suggests they want higher thinking capability. Let me check if there's a way to increase thinking or use a different model.\n\nFrom the session_status output I saw earlier:\n- Model: kimi-coding/k2p5\n- Think: low\n\nThe user could:\n1. Use kimi-coding/kimi-k2-thinking (the default which might have different characteristics)\n2. Increase thinking level from \"low\" to \"high\" or \"on\"\n3. Use a different model entirely\n\nBut I should be honest about what's available. Based on the context, the main options are:\n- kimi-coding/k2p5 (current)\n- kimi-coding/kimi-k2-thinking (default)\n\nThe user might also be able to use other models through OpenClaw, but those are the main Kimi ones mentioned.\n\nActually, looking at the system prompt again:\n\"Model Aliases\nPrefer aliases when specifying model overrides; full provider/model is also accepted.\n- Kimi for Coding: kimi-coding/k2p5\"\n\nSo kimi-coding/k2p5 is the \"Kimi for Coding\" alias. The default is kimi-coding/kimi-k2-thinking.\n\nI should explain the options:\n1. Switch to kimi-k2-thinking (the default)\n2. Increase thinking level (not a model change, but changes behavior)\n3. Check if other models are available through their system\n\nBut I should be practical - the user is asking what THEY can select. I should tell them about the thinking level option and the alternative Kimi model.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Die Modelle, die du zur Verfügung hast, basieren auf deiner OpenClaw-Konfiguration. Basierend auf dem, was ich sehe:\n\n## Verfügbare Modelle in deiner Session\n\n| Modell | Status | Beschreibung |\n|--------|--------|--------------|\n| `kimi-coding/k2p5` | ✅ Aktuell | Kimi for Coding - schnell, präzise |\n| `kimi-coding/kimi-k2-thinking` | ✅ Verfügbar | Standard-Modell mit \"thinking\" Fähigkeit |\n\n## Stärkere Optionen\n\n### 1. **Thinking-Level erhöhen** (Kein Modellwechsel nötig)\nStatt ein anderes Modell zu wählen, kannst du das **Thinking-Level** erhöhen:\n\n```\n/reasoning\n```\noder\n```\n/thinking on\n```\n\nDas aktiviert den \"Chain-of-Thought\" Modus - das Modell \"denkt\" lauter und ausführlicher, bevor es antwortet. Das ist oft effektiver als ein Modellwechsel.\n\n### 2. **Auf Standard-Modell wechseln**\n```\n/model kimi-coding/kimi-k2-thinking\n```\n\nDas ist dein Default-Modell (laut System-Konfiguration). Es kann sich anders verhalten als k2p5.\n\n## Wichtiger Hinweis\n\nDie wirklich \"starken\" Modelle (wie GPT-4, Claude 3 Opus, etc.) hängen davon ab, **welche API-Keys in deiner OpenClaw-Konfiguration hinterlegt sind**. \n\nPrüfe mit:\n```\nopenclaw config list\n```\n\noder schau in deine OpenClaw-Config-Dateien nach verfügbaren Providern (OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.).\n\n**Soll ich das Thinking-Level auf \"high\" setzen?** Das würde sofort mehr \"Berechnungsleistung\" geben, ohne das Modell zu wechseln."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":4969,"output":1037,"cacheRead":198144,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":204150,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774481164219}}
