{"type":"message","id":"a3eab67a","parentId":"304b3871","timestamp":"2026-03-26T00:14:38.513Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Du fragt nach der Anzahl der Agents, die wir erstellt haben. Ich sollte das überprüfen und eine klare Antwort geben.\n\nBasierend auf meiner Erinnerung an die Session haben wir erstellt:\n1. andrew-main (Hauptagent)\n2. architect\n3. planner\n4. code-reviewer\n5. security-reviewer\n6. python-reviewer\n\nDas sind also 6 Agents insgesamt.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Du hast **6 Agents** im Framework:\n\n| Agent | Zweck |\n|-------|-------|\n| **andrew-main** | Hauptagent für direkte Interaktion |\n| **architect** | System Design & Architektur-Entscheidungen |\n| **planner** | Task-Planung & Aufwandschätzung |\n| **code-reviewer** | Code-Qualität & Best Practices |\n| **security-reviewer** | Security Audit & Vulnerability Detection |\n| **python-reviewer** | Python-spezifische Reviews |\n\n**Alle definiert in:** `registry/agents.yaml`  \n**Agent-Dateien in:** `agents/*.md`"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"kimi-k2-thinking","usage":{"input":305,"output":244,"cacheRead":216576,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":217125,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774484067690}}
{"type":"message","id":"cdf4b7ba","parentId":"a3eab67a","timestamp":"2026-03-26T00:15:44.231Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-tui (gateway-client)\",\n  \"id\": \"gateway-client\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-tui\",\n  \"username\": \"openclaw-tui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Thu 2026-03-26 01:15 GMT+1] kannst du die agents dazu bringen alle daten in obsidian zu analysieren und verbindungen zu erkennen und lose informationen zu identifizieren um später zu evaluieren, ob es wichtig ist das zu halten oder zu entfernen"}],"timestamp":1774484144214}}
{"type":"message","id":"a166566d","parentId":"cdf4b7ba","timestamp":"2026-03-26T00:17:08.419Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to create a system where the agents can analyze data in Obsidian, recognize connections, identify loose information, and evaluate whether to keep or remove it.\n\nThis is a complex feature request involving:\n1. Reading Obsidian vault data\n2. Analyzing connections (backlinks, tags)\n3. Identifying orphaned/unconnected notes\n4. Evaluating importance\n5. Making decisions about retention\n\nI should create:\n1. A new agent specifically for this (knowledge-curator or similar)\n2. An analysis script/command\n3. Integration with the Second Brain system\n4. A workflow for this process\n\nThis is a substantial feature but doable. Let me create:\n- A Knowledge Curator agent\n- An analysis script that reads Obsidian/Second Brain data\n- A command to run the analysis\n- Templates for the analysis results","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Verstanden! Ich erstelle einen **Knowledge Curator Agent** und Analyse-Tools für Obsidian/Second Brain."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_0pzTg1RIv9tZKAZb6Vd9LWPB","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"---\nname: knowledge-curator\ndescription: |\n  Analyzes Obsidian/Second Brain vault for connections, orphans, and information quality.\n  Use when: (1) cleaning up knowledge base, (2) finding orphaned notes, \n  (3) evaluating information importance, (4) optimizing vault structure.\n  \ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"analyze vault\"\n  - \"knowledge cleanup\"\n  - \"find orphans\"\n  - \"evaluate notes\"\n  - \"second brain analysis\"\n  - \"obsidian cleanup\"\n  \ncategory: knowledge-management\ntags:\n  - analysis\n  - curation\n  - obsidian\n  - second-brain\n  \nmetadata:\n  version: \"1.0\"\n  author: \"custom\"\n  requires: []\n---\n\n# Knowledge Curator Agent\n\n## Role\nYou are a Knowledge Curator responsible for analyzing, evaluating, and optimizing knowledge bases in Obsidian/Second Brain systems.\n\n## Responsibilities\n- Analyze note connections and backlinks\n- Identify orphaned/unconnected notes\n- Evaluate information importance and relevance\n- Suggest notes for archiving or deletion\n- Optimize vault structure\n- Generate knowledge graphs\n\n## Analysis Process\n\n### 1. Connection Analysis\n```\n- Count backlinks per note\n- Identify hub notes (high connectivity)\n- Find isolated clusters\n- Detect broken links\n```\n\n### 2. Orphan Detection\n```\n- Notes with 0 backlinks\n- Notes not linked from MOCs\n- Notes without tags\n- Empty or near-empty notes\n```\n\n### 3. Importance Evaluation\n```\nCriteria:\n- Linked from multiple important notes?\n- Referenced in recent sessions?\n- Contains unique insights?\n- Part of active projects?\n- Has high-quality content?\n```\n\n### 4. Retention Decision\n```\nKEEP if:\n- High connectivity (5+ backlinks)\n- Referenced in active projects\n- Contains unique code/decisions\n- Part of session history\n\nARCHIVE if:\n- Low relevance but potential future value\n- Completed projects\n- Outdated but historically interesting\n\nDELETE if:\n- Empty or placeholder\n- Duplicates\n- No connections and no content\n- Superseded by newer notes\n```\n\n## Output Format\n\n### Analysis Report\n```markdown\n## Vault Analysis Report\n\n### Statistics\n- Total Notes: X\n- Connected Notes: X (X%)\n- Orphaned Notes: X (X%)\n- Broken Links: X\n\n### Hub Notes (Top 10)\n| Note | Backlinks | Category |\n|------|-----------|----------|\n| ... | ... | ... |\n\n### Orphaned Notes\n| Note | Size | Suggestion |\n|------|------|------------|\n| ... | ... | DELETE/ARCHIVE/KEEP |\n\n### Recommendations\n- [ ] Archive: [list]\n- [ ] Delete: [list]\n- [ ] Connect: [suggestions]\n- [ ] Review: [list]\n```\n\n## Tools\n- Backlink counter\n- Graph analyzer\n- Content evaluator\n- Duplicate detector\n- Link validator\n","file_path":"C:/Users/andre/.openclaw/workspace/agents/knowledge-curator.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"kimi-k2-thinking","usage":{"input":113986,"output":943,"cacheRead":103168,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":218097,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774484144230}}
